<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

<div id="accordion1" class="accordion">
  <div class="accordion-group">
    <div class="accordion-heading">
      <a href="#collapse1" data-parent="#accordion2" data-toggle="collapse" class="accordion-toggle">
        <h4>
          What's this all about?
        </h4>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-body collapse in" id="collapse1">
      <div class="accordion-inner">
        <p>
        Three and a half million fast food workers in America work at or close
        to minimum wage. With an average age of 28, they are adults, trying to
        support families. They are doing what workers in other industries in America
        and around the world have always done: join together to ask for higher
        pay. We want to help.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="accordion-group">
    <div class="accordion-heading">
      <a href="#collapse2" data-parent="#accordion2" data-toggle="collapse" class="accordion-toggle">
        <h4>
          Can I really help?
        </h4>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-body collapse" id="collapse2">
      <div class="accordion-inner">
        <p>
        In the 30's and 40's when America's industrial workers organized to create
        our middle class, workers were sometimes 100 thousand in a single facility.
        Communication was easier then. Until now, Fast Food Workers were too scattered
        to come together and organize. The Internet and mobile phones has tipped
        the balance for this industry. But only a small fraction of workers have
        become connected to the movement. We're seeking supporters to connect thousands
        of restaurants with this movement.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="accordion-group">
