          If fast food workers make $15/hr, how much more will people have to pay
          for a Big Mac?
        </h4>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-body collapse" id="collapse4">
      <div class="accordion-inner">
        <p>
        There have been several analyses of this question. Ask ten economists,
        and you'll get ten different answers. Here are some facts though: Labor
        is not the only cost in the price of your meal. When McDonalds pays its
        CEO more, that too creates pressure on the price of your kid's Happy Meal
        -- same for when it invests in new stores and equippment, profit distributions
        to shareholders, donations to charity, etc.... But let's say people had
        to pay 50 cents more for a meal so that we could have a strong middle class
        again in this country -- wouldn't that be worth it?
        </p>
      </div>
